entries.femaleVariant: Oh shit. Sig's... an NUS comms frequency.
Incoming… in forty-five secs, no more.
Need to move on quietly, V. Another fuckup and we're done for.
Uh-huh. Preppin' to blow in here with all they got.
entries.maleVariant: Mhm. Preppin' to blow in here with all they got.

entries.femaleVariant: By the way, great work downstairs. Flitted through like a super spy ghost, full pro.
Fuck me. FIA'll find us – Reed said so.
What's goin' on, what're they up to?
Four assault choppers incoming, masked transponder sigs. Don't want to reveal they're NUSA.
NUS combat choppers buzzin' the Free City of NC. Shit's heatin' up.
Cover's been blown on a handful. OA won't get a word out of them, I guarantee it.
They could dismantle this place, take the parts back to Washington, no one'd be the wiser.
Does Orbital Air know the stakes?
We've confirmed V's presence here at NCX.
They triggered the alarm but failed to find V.
Probably too weak to get around on 'er own. Most likely she's waiting somewhere, concealed.
Those still undercover are looking for Songbird.
We'll talk about operational errors later.
Fine, have them all engage, get the party started.
Have you breached the Orbital Air datafort?
So I decided for you and brought support.
No, Sol. You lost control, way back. It's time you acknowledged that.
I know you care about the girl, like her.
I get that you want to protect her. But your duty, first and foremost, is to your country.
The project she was part of… stays well under wraps, none of it leaks.
Ah, Rosalind Myers, her true face.
Just so you know, this isn't any easier for me, Reed. I liked the girl, trusted her. But with some choices, there's no way back.
We are fucked… every which way possible.
I managed to reach the roof – lower bit, though. Need your help to climb higher and join you.
Asking for help… never was your strong suit.
Fuck the one on her billboards.
Songbird's made her choice. Now she needs to learn what the consequences are.
Relax. I'm here and stayin'. They're not gettin' you.
Hasn't yet, let's keep it that way.
You don't know 'er. I mean, to satisfy her lust for revenge, she'd pull me outta hell.
Got a light ahead. Security. Hold up a sec…
FIA must've been on you since you went through security.
Have to try harder. Sly and smooth.
Yeah. V got through security based on a false ID.
They'll be here any sec, comin' to get us. Hurry.
Catching a radio sig. Shit... encrypted channel.
Grab one of the blades. I'll squeeze through.
Myers is desperate. Desperate peeps make mistakes.
What's it matter, really? Could both be dead and gone in moments.
They're gonna see you! Come on, take cover!
If our little bird lands in the wrong hands… I don't want to think what will happen.
All that – we're the only ones privy.
It would destroy the NUS. It's not a risk I'm willing to take.
No risks. That's how it'll be.
Ugh, just a little more! Argh!
Just tired. Your chromed ass weighs a bit.
I'm fine. Don't worry about me.
Barely clingin' onto life, both of us.
Stop it. It'll be over soon. Thanks in no small part to you.
Shape you're in, can't possibly hope to walk a high-wire.
No plan's my favorite way to go. Need a few minutes.
It's a hundred twenty, thirty feet. Doable.
Givin' you just one, no more.
The NUSA'll wind up in everyone's sights – Orbital Air's, that of any corps pullin' strings in NC.
She's a step, maybe two, from sparkin' the next war. A war she can't win, even with Militech pilin' on forces and arms.
You are boardin' that fuckin' shuttle. Promise you that.
entries.maleVariant: You're boardin' that fuckin' shuttle. Promise you that.

entries.femaleVariant: OK, moved on. Alert, now — eyes and ears.
Move, go! They're gonna spot us.
Need to delta through fast. Before all hell breaks loose.
Train ride to the launchpad, that's all. Just need to blast through the Tycho Terminal first.
OK, back to the terminal now.
Put you on that shuttle – 's all we need to do. And that'll be that.
entries.maleVariant: Put you on the shuttle – 's all we need to do. And that'll be that.

entries.femaleVariant: No way this'll hold the weight.
I can hear you. You know that, right?
I authorize you to take any and all necessary action. Just try not to shoot 'er in the head.
You heard me. But no matter. I know what I have to do and I'll do it.
NCX is not technically part of NC. Exterritorial, neutral zone. This is Myers basically blowin' off international law and agreements.
Move it, V. Scan the roof for somethin'.
Reed just stabbed you in the back.
Didn't think Reed'd fold that easily, sell out straight.
I was afraid to trust him, just couldn't. Understand why now?
Think he plain lied? Said he wanted to help you, stressed it.
Was lyin' to himself. Desperate to believe he wouldn't have to choose between me 'n' Myers.
But his and the NUS's national conscience – one and the same.
Next time… just shouldn't be a next time, not like this.
Myers's all in,  ain't takin' any prisoners.
